  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Eliza Frances Meriam called. &quot;She will make a fine Treasurer.&quot; Anne Warren Weston attended the monthly concert (of prayer for the slaves). Captain William Ladd made a &quot;most peeling speech. I never heard such daubing with untempered mortar. O. Johnson discomfitted him altogether.&quot; William (R.) Chapman prayed. Anne mistrusts him a little. She was shown about a hospital by a Dr. Whipple. &quot;I think he respects me with a preference. What think you of turning my attention that way?&quot; She describes a conversation with a clergyman, Dr. (Edward J.?) Taylor, who &quot;is very narrow intellectually.&quot; J.A. Collins was here, &quot;settling&quot; with H.G. Chapman. &quot;The other Fair is to be held the 17, 18, 19th of Nov. this Chapman told me--I suppose ours will be announced soon.&quot; Mary Parker is ill, probably mostly from worry.</subfield>
  </datafield>
